theorem interior_diff_subset_diff_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A \ B) ⊆ interior A \ closure B := by
  classical
  intro x hx
  -- `x` lies in `interior A` because `A \ B ⊆ A`.
  have hxA : x ∈ interior A :=
    (interior_mono (Set.diff_subset : (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ A)) hx
  -- Show that `x ∉ closure B`.
  have hxNotClB : x ∉ closure B := by
    by_contra hxCl
    -- Choose an open set `U` with `x ∈ U ⊆ A \ B`.
    rcases mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds.1 hx with ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUsub⟩
    -- Since `x ∈ closure B`, every such `U` meets `B`.
    have hNonempty : ((U : Set X) ∩ B).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff.1 hxCl) U hUopen hxU
    rcases hNonempty with ⟨y, hyU, hyB⟩
    -- But `U ⊆ A \ B`, so `y ∉ B`, contradiction.
    have : y ∈ A \ B := hUsub hyU
    exact (this.2 hyB)
  exact ⟨hxA, hxNotClB⟩

theorem P1_inter_right_open {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : Topology.P1 A) (hB_open : IsOpen B) :
    Topology.P1 (A ∩ B) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hA ⊢
  intro x hxAB
  rcases hxAB with ⟨hxA, hxB⟩
  -- `x` lies in the closure of `interior A` by `P1`.
  have hx_clA : x ∈ closure (interior A) := hA hxA
  -- We show that `x` belongs to `closure (interior (A ∩ B))`
  -- using the neighbourhood characterization of `closure`.
  have : x ∈ closure (interior (A ∩ B)) := by
    apply (mem_closure_iff).2
    intro U hU_open hxU
    -- Consider the open neighbourhood `U ∩ B` of `x`.
    have hUB_open : IsOpen (U ∩ B) := hU_open.inter hB_open
    have hxUB : x ∈ U ∩ B := ⟨hxU, hxB⟩
    -- Since `x ∈ closure (interior A)`, this neighbourhood meets `interior A`.
    have hNonempty : ((U ∩ B) ∩ interior A).Nonempty :=
      ((mem_closure_iff).1 hx_clA) (U ∩ B) hUB_open hxUB
    -- Extract a witness `y`.
    rcases hNonempty with ⟨y, h_y⟩
    rcases h_y with ⟨⟨hyU, hyB⟩, hyIntA⟩
    -- Show that `y ∈ interior (A ∩ B)`.
    have hyIntAB : y ∈ interior (A ∩ B) := by
      -- The set `interior A ∩ B` is open, contained in `A ∩ B`, and contains `y`.
      have hOpen' : IsOpen (interior A ∩ B) :=
        isOpen_interior.inter hB_open
      have hSub : (interior A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ B := by
        intro z hz
        exact ⟨(interior_subset hz.1), hz.2⟩
      have hyMem : y ∈ interior A ∩ B := ⟨hyIntA, hyB⟩
      exact (interior_maximal hSub hOpen') hyMem
    -- Provide the required witness in `U ∩ interior (A ∩ B)`.
    exact ⟨y, ⟨hyU, hyIntAB⟩⟩
  exact this

theorem interior_union_left_open {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen A) :
    interior (A ∪ B) = A ∪ interior B := by
  classical
  -- We show mutual inclusion of the two sets.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` direction
    intro x hxInt
    -- If `x ∈ A`, we are done.
    by_cases hAx : x ∈ A
    · exact Or.inl hAx
    -- Otherwise, `x ∉ A`; we prove `x ∈ interior B`.
    · -- Obtain an open neighbourhood `U` of `x` with `U ⊆ A ∪ B`.
      rcases mem_interior.1 hxInt with ⟨U, hUopen, hUsub, hxU⟩
      -- Consider the set `V = U \ A`, still open and containing `x`.
      have hVopen : IsOpen (U \ A) := hUopen.diff hA
      have hxV : x ∈ U \ A := by
        refine ⟨hxU, ?_⟩
        simpa [hAx] using hAx
      -- Show that `V ⊆ B`.
      have hVsubB : (U \ A : Set X) ⊆ B := by
        intro y hyV
        have hyU : y ∈ U := hyV.1
        have hyA : y ∉ A := hyV.2
        have : y ∈ A ∪ B := hUsub hyU
        cases this with
        | inl hInA => exact (hyA hInA).elim
        | inr hInB => exact hInB
      -- Hence `x ∈ interior B`.
      have hxIntB : x ∈ interior B := mem_interior.2 ⟨U \ A, hVopen, hVsubB, hxV⟩
      exact Or.inr hxIntB
  · -- `⊇` direction
    intro x hx
    -- The set `A ∪ interior B` is open and contained in `A ∪ B`.
    have hOpen : IsOpen (A ∪ interior B) := hA.union isOpen_interior
    have hSub : (A ∪ interior B : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B := by
      intro y hy
      cases hy with
      | inl hAy => exact Or.inl hAy
      | inr hIntBy =>
          exact Or.inr ((interior_subset : interior B ⊆ B) hIntBy)
    -- Use openness and containment to deduce the required membership.
    have hInner : (A ∪ interior B : Set X) ⊆ interior (A ∪ B) :=
      interior_maximal hSub hOpen
    exact hInner hx

theorem closure_union_closure_left {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (closure A ∪ B : Set X) = closure (A ∪ B) := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  ·
    -- Show `closure (closure A ∪ B)` is contained in `closure (A ∪ B)`.
    have hSub : (closure A ∪ B : Set X) ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
      intro x hx
      cases hx with
      | inl hClA =>
          have : closure A ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) :=
            closure_mono (Set.subset_union_left : (A : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B)
          exact this hClA
      | inr hB =>
          exact subset_closure (Or.inr hB)
    have : closure (closure A ∪ B) ⊆ closure (closure (A ∪ B)) :=
      closure_mono hSub
    simpa [closure_closure] using this
  ·
    -- Show `closure (A ∪ B)` is contained in `closure (closure A ∪ B)`.
    have hSub : (A ∪ B : Set X) ⊆ closure A ∪ B := by
      intro x hx
      cases hx with
      | inl hA   => exact Or.inl (subset_closure hA)
      | inr hB   => exact Or.inr hB
    exact closure_mono hSub
